<a name="Option Files">

<H1>Option Files
</H1>


<P>
It is recommended to write an <I><A name="index_106_110"></A>option file</I> for each of your PerlPoint presentations or documents. Just write down all options you need in file, line by line:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
 # Option file for my cool presentation:

 --title &quot;How to make Slides&quot;
 --target_dir ./pp-slides
 --style big_blue
 --style_dir /home/PerlPoint/pp2html_styles
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>
Then you can call <CODE>pp2html</CODE> with <CODE>@options.cfg</CODE>
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  pp2html @options.cfg how-to-make-slides.pp
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>
For more information about option files please refer to the <B>Getopt::ArgvFile</B> manpage:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
 perldoc Getopt::ArgvFile
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>
